OL,3,CInfected blood victim says
OL,4,Ccompensation 'isn't good enough' as
OL,5,Cwait goes on
OL,7,FBeatrice Morgan, senior associate
OL,8,Fsolicitor at Leigh Day, which
OL,9,Frepresents dozens of victims, said:
OL,10,F"We do have some concerns, still,
OL,11,Fabout the proposed scheme and we
OL,12,Funderstand that there's detail to come.
OL,14,F"There are quite a few of our clients
OL,15,Fwho haven't been eligible for any kind
OL,16,Fof support payments so far, and
OL,17,Fhaven't received that compensation sum
OL,18,Fthat was delivered last year, so there
OL,19,Fare details in relation to the
OL,20,Fadministration of the scheme that are
OL,21,Fyet to become clear.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/18
